INSERT INTO "tbarticle" VALUES ('46', '	Then everybody star ', '1', '	Then everybody started shouting ''B-B! B-B!'' again and again, slowly, with a long pause between the first B and the second. Of course Winston shouted too – you had to. But there was a second when the look on his face showed what he was thinking. And at that exact moment his eyes met O''Brien''s. ', '2015-11-22 00:00:00', 't', 'some image', '''everybodi'':2 ''star'':3', '''b'':6,7,9,10,22 ''b-b'':5,8 ''brien'':60 ''cours'':27 ''everybodi'':2 ''exact'':54 ''eye'':57 ''face'':45 ''first'':21 ''long'':17 ''look'':42 ''met'':58 ''moment'':55 ''o'':59 ''paus'':18 ''second'':25,39 ''shout'':4,29 ''show'':46 ''slowli'':14 ''start'':3 ''think'':50 ''winston'':28 ''–'':31');
INSERT INTO "tbarticle" VALUES ('47', '	O''Brien was pushing ', '3', '	O''Brien was pushing his glasses up his nose. But Winston knew – yes he knew – that O''Brien was thinking the same thing as he was. ''I am with you,'' O''Brien seemed to say to him. ''I hate all this too.'' And then the moment of intelligence was gone and O''Brien''s face looked like everybody else''s. ', '2015-11-22 00:00:00', 't', 'some image', '''brien'':2 ''o'':1 ''push'':4', '''brien'':2,20,34,55 ''els'':61 ''everybodi'':60 ''face'':57 ''glass'':6 ''gone'':52 ''hate'':41 ''intellig'':50 ''knew'':12,16 ''like'':59 ''look'':58 ''moment'':48 ''nose'':9 ''o'':1,19,33,54 ''push'':4 ''say'':37 ''seem'':35 ''thing'':25 ''think'':22 ''winston'':11 ''yes'':14 ''–'':13,17');
INSERT INTO "tbarticle" VALUES ('48', '	Winston wrote the d ', '6', '	Winston wrote the date in his diary: April 4th 1984. Then he stopped. He did not know definitely that this was 1984. He was thirty-nine, he believed – he had been born in 1944 or 1945. But nobody could be sure of dates, not really. ', '2015-11-22 00:00:00', 't', 'some image', '''d'':4 ''winston'':1 ''wrote'':2', '''1944'':36 ''1945'':38 ''1984'':10,22 ''4th'':9 ''april'':8 ''believ'':29 ''born'':34 ''could'':41 ''date'':4,45 ''definit'':18 ''diari'':7 ''know'':17 ''nine'':27 ''nobodi'':40 ''realli'':47 ''stop'':13 ''sure'':43 ''thirti'':26 ''thirty-nin'':25 ''winston'':1 ''wrote'':2 ''–'':30');
INSERT INTO "tbarticle" VALUES ('49', '	''Who am I writing t ', '1', '	''Who am I writing this diary for?'' he asked himself suddenly. For the future, for the unborn. But if the future was like the present, it would not listen to him. And if it was different, his situation would be meaningless. ', '2015-11-22 00:00:00', 't', 'some image', '''write'':4', '''ask'':9 ''diari'':6 ''differ'':36 ''futur'':14,21 ''like'':23 ''listen'':29 ''meaningless'':41 ''present'':25 ''situat'':38 ''sudden'':11 ''unborn'':17 ''would'':27,39 ''write'':4');
INSERT INTO "tbarticle" VALUES ('50', '	The telescreen was  ', '4', '	The telescreen was playing marching music. What had he intended to say? Winston stared at the page, then began to write: Freedom is the freedom to say that two and two make four. If you have that, everything else follows... He stopped. Should he go on? If he wrote more or did not write more, the result would be the same. The Thought Police would get him. Even before he wrote anything, his crime was clear. Thoughtcrime, they called it. ', '2015-11-22 00:00:00', 't', 'some image', '''telescreen'':2', '''anyth'':72 ''began'':19 ''call'':79 ''clear'':76 ''crime'':74 ''els'':39 ''even'':68 ''everyth'':38 ''follow'':40 ''four'':33 ''freedom'':22,25 ''get'':66 ''go'':45 ''intend'':10 ''make'':32 ''march'':5 ''music'':6 ''page'':17 ''play'':4 ''polic'':64 ''result'':57 ''say'':12,27 ''stare'':14 ''stop'':42 ''telescreen'':2 ''thought'':63 ''thoughtcrim'':77 ''two'':29,31 ''winston'':13 ''would'':58,65 ''write'':21,54 ''wrote'':49,71');
